## Implementation Practices and Tools

| Practice/Tool                      | Purpose/Benefit                                                                                  | Example/Source                                                                                 |
|----------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Standardized hand-off protocols   | Ensure consistent, complete information transfer                                                | Use of SBAR (Situation-Background-Assessment-Recommendation) or electronic hand-off tools ([Wolters Kluwer, 2019](https://www.wolterskluwer.com/en/expert-insights/best-practices-for-safe-and-successful-care-transitions)) |
| Interdisciplinary team meetings   | Facilitate real-time communication and problem-solving                                         | Daily huddles or transition rounds involving nurses, physicians, pharmacists, social workers ([Patel & Landrigan, 2019](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31230621/)) |
| Care Transition Navigators        | Coordinate complex transitions and advocate for patient needs                                  | Use of dedicated staff to manage inter-facility transfers and discharge planning ([Connect Care Manual, 2025](https://manual.connect-care.ca/workflows/patient-movement/Interfacility-Transfers)) |
| Electronic Health Records (EHR)   | Provide accessible, up-to-date patient information across settings                              | Integration of EHR systems to allow seamless data sharing among providers ([PSQH, 2025](https://www.psqh.com/analysis/understanding-care-transitions-as-a-patient-safety-issue/)) |
| Patient and caregiver education   | Enhance understanding, self-management, and adherence                                         | CTI model’s coaching sessions and educational materials ([Care Transitions Health, 2025](https://caretransitions.health/about)) |
| Leadership training programs      | Develop skills in communication, collaboration, and quality improvement                        | Workshops and seminars for nurse managers and clinical leaders ([Martin et al., 2010](https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-319-71042-6_12)) |

